        <p class="metadata">Posted by Nico Edtinger (nico) on 2008-04-22T11:15:39.000+0000</p> 
        <div class="body">
            <p>We don't delete any messages unless you call removeMessage(), we are also not changing any flags, but an IMAP server will remove the recent flag. The option "keep mails on server" in your typical mail client does just this - do a second request to delete the message or change flags. I thought about adding such an option (mark as read/delete if fetched), but haven't done so yet (and it won't be the default).</p>

<p>You mentioned google any I guess the problem might be your gmail settings. Under "Forwarding and POP/IMAP" there is this option "When messages are accessed with POP" and if it's set to delete that's what it'll do.</p>

